@node "feature_list" "Mathador V1.1 Feature list              "
@next "introduction"
@prev "distribution"
@{bg shine}Feature list: Mathador V1.1@{bg back}

Here is a list of the main features of the program Mathador to let you see at
a glance what it can do for you.

 |> Scientific calculator for students (physics, mathematics...)

 |> Can do calculations using complex numbers and functions

 |> Easy notation of functions and variables

 |> Screenmode-Requester for use with graphics cards (needs KS 3.0)

 |> Font-Requester gives the personal touch for Mathador

 |> Many TOOLTYPES to adjust the appearance of Mathador

 |> Shell command options (including help option -h or ?)

 |> Scientific constants predefined in two physical unit systems (SI, cgs)

 |> Additional user definable constants (no limit)

 |> Trigonometric mode switch (radians and degrees)

 |> Adjustable accuracy in display and calculations

 |> 10 easy definable and constantly visible subformulas

 |> Standard keyboard window (for mouse enthusiasts)

 |> Standard functions window (with a lot of complex standard functions)

 |> Help texts shown immediately beneath chosen function or constant

 |> Scientific functions window (with more complicated functions,
    like complex Besselfunctions, Fresnel integrals, Complete elliptic
    integrals, Gammafunction, ...)

 |> Scientific constants window (with a lot of physical constants)

 |> Self definable expressions window (allows to define new functions
    and constants including descriptions of your own)

 |> Console edit window for keyboard input including line buffer history

 |> Log window to save all done calculations

 |> Easy cut and paste of all expressions within Mathador and outside

 |> ARexx port to control Mathador from external programs

 |> Calculations and expressions can be loaded from and saved to
    project files

 |> Mathador uses mathador.library

 |> Workbench 2.0 necessary (for full functionality 3.0 upto 3.1)

 |> MUI-Version of Mathador in preparation

 |> Tested with enforcer and mungwall
@endnode

@node "introduction" "Introduction              "
@prev "feature_list"
@{bg shine}Introduction: Mathador V1.1@{bg back}

Mathador is a very useful program for scientists, physicists, students and all
those who have to deal with complex numbers and more or less complicated
functions. It is also usable by people who want to make only trivial
calculations with convenience.

Apart from direct attention, Mathador can also be controlled by an external
program using its ARexx port. So for example if your favorite math program
lacks some complex functions you can send a simple ARexx command to Mathador
and get the desired result into your program (if it has an ARexx port, too, of
course).

Mathador uses the Amiga resident "mathador.library" which offers the full set
of predefined functions and constants.

If you want to define your own functions or constants and make them
permanently available, you can use the "Self Defined Expression Window" of
Mathador.

If you want to plot complicated diagrams of your functions defined in Mathador
you can use the separate program PolyGraph, which will also be available soon
on Aminet as PolyLab21.0.lha (older version PolyLab20.0.lha is already in
Aminet and plots very well, too).

The program (in MathadorV1.1.lha) is SHAREWARE and somehow crippled. In the
DEMO-Version it is not possible to save calculations and from time to time
nerv-requesters appear.

The archive MathadorV1.1.lha contains only a short description of the program.
If you want to get the whole information please register and pay the shareware
fee. Please fill in the file "@{"OrderForm" link "orderform" 0}", print it out and send it to the
author.

If you are familiar with scientific numbers and functions, it will be no
problem to use Mathador, since the program and its functions are easily
understandable. The documentation for the ARexx commands will only be
available for registered users.
@endnode

