@node "TestMath-01.rexx" "TestMath-01.rexx"
@next "arexx"
@prev "arexx_examples"
 /* TestMath-01.rexx */

 say "This ARexx-Program shows as an"
 say "example a few commands of Mathador:"
 say "Error checking is NOT done here."
 say ""
 say "'MathadorToFront'"
 say "'MathadorToBack'"
 say "'Calc'."
 say ""

 signal ON BREAK_C
 address 'Mathador.Host'
 options results

 'MathadorToFront'

 say 'Next command is: MathadorToBack'
 pull yes

 'MathadorToBack'
 say 'Enter an expression...'
 parse pull expression

 'Calc' expression
 say "The result from Mathador is:"
 say result

 do forever
    say "Please enter an ARexx-command for Mathador (exit->EXIT)"
    drop cmd
    parse pull cmd
    if  cmd = "EXIT" then leave
    drop result
    cmd
    if  rc < 1  then do
       say "The result from Mathador is:" result
    end
    else do
       say "Mathador-Error:" rc
    end
 end

 exit
@endnode

@node "print_res" "Print results from Mathador"
@next "arexx"
@prev "start_math"
@{bg shine}Printing results with Mathador V1.1:@{bg back}

There is a menu item called "Settings/Printer Log". If you switch it on, you
will get each line of calculation printed on your preference printer. If you
do not want printings any more, switch "Settings/Printer Log" off.

There is another way to print results after calculations have been done with
Mathador. There is a menu item called "Windows/Mathador Log" you can use. It
opens a window called "Mathador Log Window" where each calculation is saved to
screen. If you are finished working with Mathador, close the main program
window. A file called "Mathador.log" will be created, where all of your
calculations are saved in ASCII format. Therefore this file can be edited with
every texteditor or printed out directly.

 A Shell command
 "@{fg shine}copy Mathador.log PRT:@{fg text}"
 will be enough to print it out.

If you make calculations that should not be saved, close the window called
"Mathador Log Window". Then, if you want to save calculations once more, open
this window again. In this way you can print out only those calculations that
you find valuable.
@endnode

